title: Cubs put squeeze on Cardinals, even NLDS with 6-3 win (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,191 Cubs put squeeze on Cardinals, even NLDS with 6-3 win (Yahoo Sports) Kyle Hendricks and Addison Russell had successful squeeze bunts and Jorge Soler capped a five-run second with a two-run homer, and the Chicago Cubs held off the St. Louis Cardinals 6-3 on Saturday night to even their NL Division Series at a game apiece. Manager Joe Maddon made all the right moves a night after the Cubs lost the opener 4-0. The usually steady NL Central champion Cardinals made two errors as the Cubs didn't hit the ball out of the infield in scoring their first three runs in the second.
